## Backend (NestJS)

- DB_SYNCHRONIZE=false — always create migration files in src/database/migrations/
- req.user.sub for user ID in JWT payload (never req.user.id)
- @Roles(...) and @Permissions(...) decorators required on every controller method
- Logger (NestJS) for all logging — never console.log()
- ConfigService for environment variables — never process.env directly
- HTTP exceptions: ConflictException, NotFoundException, ForbiddenException, BadRequestException, UnauthorizedException
- Routes: kebab-case plural nouns (/user-profiles not /userProfiles, /activity-logs not /activityLog)
- AuditService.log() on every CREATE, UPDATE, DELETE operation
- All database tables: snake_case plural names, UUID primary keys
- All column names: snake_case via explicit { name: '...' } TypeORM option
- Migrations: always generate file, review before running, never rely on synchronize: true
- DTOs: class-validator on all fields, UpdateDto always extends PartialType(CreateDto)
- ParseUUIDPipe on all :id route parameters
- @ApiProperty / @ApiPropertyOptional on all DTO and entity properties
- @Exclude() + select: false on sensitive entity fields
- No :any TypeScript types — use proper interfaces or unknown
- Tenant isolation: always filter queries by tenantId from JWT, never from request body
